                       java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Double> distList,

        produces a ConcavityRegion
        Parameters:
        startX - x-Coordinate of the StartingPoint of the ConcavityRegion
        startY - y-Coordinate of the StartingPoint of the ConcavityRegion
        endX - x-Coordinate of the endPoint of the ConcavityRegion
        endY - y-Coordinate of the endPoint of the ConcavityRegion
        boundaryPointList - List of all Pixels of the part of the boundary included by the ConcavityRegion
        distList - List of the concavityDepth of all points of the part of the boundary included by the ConcavityRegion
        max - largest concavityDepth of the ConcavityRegion
        maxIndex - index of the point with the largest concavityDepth based by the boundaryPointList
